File: South Africa's forward Percy Tau. Phill Magakoe / AFP JOHANNESBURG - Bafana Bafana has been dealt a massive blow ahead of their international friendly against Uganda on Thursday. Star striker Percy Tau will miss the match after testing positive for COVID-19. Tau will be joined by SuperSport midfielder Teboho Mokoena on the sideline after Mokoena also tested positive. Both players will be quarantined and will miss the match along with Mokoena’s midfield partner Sipho Mbule. There are also injury concerns over Mamelodi Sundowns’ Mosa Lebusa and Rivaldo Coetzee.